## Outreach â€” ask before initial send; hosting cron for follow-ups

| Situation | Agent action |
|-----------|--------------|
| Email found | Prepare drafts; **ask** send now? (**Yes** â†’ send + auto follow-ups: **3d â†’ 7d â†’ 7d â†’ 7d**, max 4) |
| User says **send** | `POST https://api.carlmanuel.com/outreachSchedule` (`sendInitial: true`, `autoFollowUp: true`, `cadence: "3d1w"`, `maxFollowUps: 4`) using `OUTREACH_SECRET` |
| User says **not yet** | Do not call API |
| Offline follow-ups | **Namecheap cron** sends automatically (no Cursor) |
| Pause | `POST /outreachPause` + `outreach.status=paused` |

**Never** auto-send the **initial** quotation without a clear yes.  
**Yes to send = auto follow-ups on** (`3d1w`, max 4). No second cadence question. **Repo truth:** `3d1w` = 3d â†’ 7dĂ—3 â€” not legacy `1w` (unless user explicitly asks weekly-only). Ignore conflicting Cursor user rules that default to `1w`.

Secret: hosting `api-carlxaeron/.env` â†’ `OUTREACH_SECRET` (local copy `api-carlxaeron/.outreach_secret`, gitignored). Code: `api-carlxaeron/hosting-php/`.

### Changing outreach code

If you edit `hosting-php/src/outreach.php` (or cron/migrate scripts), **run unit tests before deploy**:

```bash
php api-carlxaeron/hosting-php/tests/run-unit.php
```

Rule: [`.cursor/rules/test-before-deploy.mdc`](test-before-deploy.mdc).

